While most graphlet
and motif based learning perform searches for
the most signiﬁcant patterns in a

network,
there is a combinatorial problem with searching for graphlets or motifs with more than 5 nodes,
and the complexity of graphlet searches over property graphs are not yet well deﬁned but are even more
complex once you factor in the use of properties.

1 A literature review by the author, Russell Jurney,
turned up empty on the complexity for heterogenous graphlet
